This thing was a beast in the snow yesterday! We took some of the @dissentoffroad rigs out for a bit of snow wheeling and "product testing" yesterday and found some DEEP snow (not pictured). The new 2023 Sequoia TRD Pro led the pack on 37" Nitto Recon Grapplers and @alphaequipt wheels. The high clearance bumper did its job and reduced the plowing effort.

Despite slick conditions and snow up halfway up the door, the Sequoia didn't falter nor did it freak out and hit us with traction nanny issues or error lights when the going got tough. Sure it got temporarily mired a few times but with good driving techniques by Ben (Dissent owner) the Sequoia was able to free itself without assistance. Color me impressed, @toyotausa

Get it while it's HOT!!!

We have decided to do a 1 time production run on the FJ60/62 front bumper. Production will be starting around Feb/March and this will likely not be made again.

It's high clearance like the rest of our designs. However, we did not go modular on this bumper like our other bumpers in order to keep a clean old-school look. Because of this, it will need to be ordered with or without a bull bar. The bull bar will not be available to be added at a later date. a smaller stinger style bar is also an option.

For this reason, we are only offering this raw, so no coating options are available for shipped orders. As a one-piece bumper, we will not be able to package it like we do the modular bumpers, so damage to the coating during shipping is difficult to avoid.

Check out our website for more details and options!

Industry Spotlight! Innovation in the off-road and overland industry is always a very good thing, and @dissentoffroad comes through in a major way with their modular rear bumper.

We are fans of dual swing out bumpers for their shorter footprint and better weight distribution when deployed, and Dissent takes it up one level by making the swing outs modular so you can customize and configure each arm to suit your needs. Modular options include a rear tire swing out, aluminum tray, or full on overland panels with the ability to mount traction boards, shovel, recovery gear, etc.

An aspect we like the most about modular swing out arms is the ability to distribute weight according to your make/model. It is advisable to have your heavier items like spare tires positioned to counter balance your gas tank placement.

Each bumper and swing out is made to order and the Dissent team has confirmed fitting with 100 & 200 Series Land Cruiser, GX470, GX460, 4th and 5th Gen 4Runner, and 3rd Gen Tacomas. Pricing for each piece (bumper & swing outs) is separate. Looking forward to seeing what the Dissent crew has in store for the future!

Photos via Dissent Offroad

Be Prepared! It may not be your own neck that needs saving. A solid winching platform is a must have when adventuring on snow-covered trails. GXMoose outfitted his 2009 Lexus GX470 with Dissent Off-Road front and rear modular bumpers, a Comeup winch, Agency6 hook and TreatyOakOffroad recovery gear.

We found this ill-equipped Tundra stuck in the snow with a snow storm on the way. Due to the high load on the winch we opted to secure the rear of the GX to a tree. Partially to test the strength of the bumpers and recovery points and because there were no nearby trees to set up a "Double Line Static Offset Anchor" winch pattern to help reduce the load on the GX.
